cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with incorporating richer structural dependencies within deep neural networks, specifically in the context of natural language processing tasks such as machine translation and question answering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the practical implementation of these models as neural network layers, which suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of graphical models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and probabilistic modeling, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The experiments also involve tasks related to computer vision, such as tree transduction, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which suggests a focus on optimization and performance, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
